		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">qtoyoda wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">enuf</div><br />PROTIP: You'll look more serious if you make an effort to 1. spell correctly, 2. use capital letters correctly, and 3. use punctuation correctly.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">the main thing i dont understand is what exactly the accumulator is.... and how it work</div><br />It's a register inside the CPU. Various instructions do arithmetic (e.g. ADC, SBC, CMP) and logical (e.g. ORA, AND, EOR), taking one operand from the accumulator and putting the result in the computer.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">im unable to do like any programming cus the A, X, and Y are all the registers</div>
<br />X and Y are often used as the indices for two arrays.

		

