	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />To learn about the "logical", see <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitwise_operation" class="postlink">Bitwise operation</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mask_%28computing%29" class="postlink">Mask</a>.
<br />
<br />Yes, the vast majority of pieces of information seen on the screen have passed through the accumulator. For example, moving an object across the screen involves loading the current position from a variable in memory into the accumulator, adding its velocity from another variable, and storing the position back to the first variable.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


